content:
Give your knowledge agents access to articles in Lightning Knowledge. Specify which agents in your company are Salesforce Knowledge users and can create, edit, archive, and delete articles.

Create user profiles with the appropriate user permissions, and then assign users to these profiles.

Available in: Lightning Experience

Salesforce Knowledge is available in Essentials and Unlimited Editions with Service Cloud.

User permissions control access to different tasks in Salesforce Knowledge. Assign permissions to agents and authors who publish, archive delete, and manage articles.

Use permission sets or custom profiles to give agents, authors, and other users the Knowledge access they need.

To see categories associated with Draft articles, standard Users must have permissions for Knowledge User and Manage Article.

Agents need the Knowledge User license to do more than read articles.

Required profile and object permissions for authoring tasks:

* Read and search published knowledge articles: Allow View Knowledge
* Read and search draft knowledge articles: Allow View Knowledge, View Draft Articles
* Attach or detach published articles: Allow View Knowledge
* Create articles: Manage Articles
* Edit draft articles: Manage Articles
* Delete draft articles: Manage Articles
* Publish articles: Manage Articles
* Archive articles: Manage Articles

Assign permissions to agents and authors who publish, archive delete, and manage articles.
title: Granting Access to Lightning Knowledge
